==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*dauba-'', from Indo-European ''*dheubh-'' ‘smoky, foggy, dim’.  Germanic cognates include Old Frisian [[daf|dāf]], Old Saxon [[dof|dōf]] (Dutch [[doof]]), Old High German [[toub]] (German [[taub]]), Old Norse [[daufr]] (Swedish [[döv]]).  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[τυφλος]] ‘blind’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /dæ:af/

===Adjective===
'''dēaf'''
# deaf

